parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to safety risks, especially at night or in hazardous locations, and can also cause inconvenience and financial losses.
symptoms: The battery light comes on
the vehicle stalls or dies
the vehicle cranks but does not start
the headlights and dashboard lights go out
the vehicle has a sudden loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the immobilizer system can cause the vehicle to not start, leading to safety risks, especially at night or in hazardous locations, and can also cause inconvenience and financial losses.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start
the immobilizer control module is faulty
the antenna ring is faulty
the transmitter and receiver are not in sync.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The battery drainage issue can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to safety risks, especially at night or in hazardous locations, and can also cause inconvenience and financial losses.
symptoms: The battery drains excessively
the vehicle stalls or dies after sitting for an extended period
the battery needs to be replaced frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hard shifting and failure of the transmission can cause loss of control, skidding, and accidents, especially in stop-and-go traffic. It can also lead to premature wear on other components and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Hard shifting between gears
especially between 1st and 2nd gear
tires skid or feel like the vehicle has been hit from behind
transmission shifts harshly
transmission failure with low mileage
vehicle drives fine at high speeds but has issues in city driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to unexpected deployments, causing injuries or distractions that can result in accidents. Additionally, faulty airbag systems can fail to deploy in crash situations, compromising the safety of occupants.
symptoms: The airbag symbol appears on the dashboard
the check engine light stays on
spontaneous airbag deployment without impact
airbag deployment in non-crash situations
inconsistent airbag deployment (e.g.
passenger airbag deploys while driver's airbag does not).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty airbag sensor can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to unexpected deployments or failures to deploy in crash situations, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag symbol appears on the dashboard
spontaneous airbag deployment without impact
airbag deployment in non-crash situations
inconsistent airbag deployment (e.g.
passenger airbag deploys while driver's airbag does not).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause a range of issues, including airbag system malfunctions, which can compromise vehicle safety.
symptoms: The check engine light stays on
electrical issues cause airbag system malfunctions
repeated electrical repairs do not resolve the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Electronic Throttle Module (ETM) can cause sudden and unexpected acceleration, loss of power, or stalling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's Check Engine Light (CEL) or Electronic Throttle Service (ETS) light illuminates
the vehicle experiences sudden and violent shuttering
the vehicle appears to stall or hesitate
the vehicle accelerates briefly or unexpectedly
the vehicle's throttle response is erratic or unresponsive.
